  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Butter a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "In a separate pan, sauté the diced onion until softened.",
    "Add the grated cheddar cheese, flour, garlic powder, nutmeg, and salt. Mix well.",
    "In a separate saucepan, heat the coconut milk over medium heat.",
    "Gradually add the chocolate chips, stirring constantly until melted.",
    "Combine the cooked onion mixture and coconut milk mixture.",
    "Layer the sliced potatoes in the prepared baking dish.",
    "Pour the onion-coconut mixture over the potatoes.",
    "Top with additional grated cheese if desired.",
    "Bake for 30-40 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the potatoes are tender.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs if desired."
